ZCZC GE26
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 112300 UTC
THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY AN AREA OF LOW
PRESSURE 1000 MBAR WILL BE CENTRED TO THE W OF FITZROY.
THE SCANDINAVIAN HIGH PRESSURE SYSTEM WILL EXTEND A RIDGE
ACROSS THE N SEA AND SCOTLAND. PRESSURE WILL BE LOW
ACROSS THE MEDITERRANEAN SEA AND TO THE NW OF ICELAND. A
SIMILAR PRESSURE PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH MONDAY AND
TUESDAY ALTHOUGH THE RIDGE AXIS WILL LIKELY DRIFT SLWY
NEWARDS ON TUESDAY AND PRESSURE WILL FALL IN FITZROY AND
TO THE W OF THE UK. A TROUGH OF LOW PRESSURE WILL DEVELOP
IN THE SERN N SEA ON TUESDAY. ON SATURDAY EVENING AND
SUNDAY NE WINDS MAY BE OCNL STRG IN DOGGER FISHER
GERMAN BIGHT HUMBER THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT. THROUGH
MONDAY WINDS WILL MOD IN THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT BUT
STRENGTHEN IN FORTIES. SIMILAR WIND STRENGTHS WILL
PERSIST THROUGH TUESDAY
